Building an inclusive society with digital technologies

Digital Books

   BrailleNet develops tools and services to improve reading for the print
   disabled. Through the BNFA digital library, BrailleNet is France's
   primary producer of accessible digital books.

AccessiWeb

   Through its AccessiWeb initative, BrailleNet offers support and a host
   of digital accessibility services built around international
   accessibility standards.

Events

   Each year BrailleNet organises a series of workshops and conferences to
   raise awareness and draw attention the latest developments in digital
   accessibility.

R&D

   To support its core missions, BrailleNet coordinates and participates
   in research projects in collaboration with research institutes,
   universities and private partners.

News

National Meeting on Accessible Digital Books

   After the success of the first national meeting on access to books and
   reading organised the 7th December 2017, BrailleNet, the
   Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes Centre for Books and Reading and the French …

   Read more

AccessiWeb workshop 25 : Assistive Technologies Today

   Cité des Sciences, Paris | Tuesday 16th October | 10am to 5pm In
   digital accessibility jargon, “assistive technologies” refers to the
   tools, applications and devices that persons with disabilities use to …

   Read more

Focus

Study day on access to books and reading for the print-disabled

   On the 7 December 2017, BrailleNet, Arald and Enssib organised a study
   day on access to books and reading for people with print disabilities.
   Over 80 publishing professionals attended the …

   Read more

